fields.name: Gothenburg
fields.description: Gothenburg is the second-largest city in Sweden, and capital of the Västra Götaland County. It has a population of approx. 1.1 million inhabitants in the metropolitan area.

fields.name: Malmö
fields.description: Malmö is the largest city in the Swedish county of Skåne. It is the third-largest city in Sweden, after Stockholm and Gothenburg, with a municipal population of 357,377 in 2022.

fields.name: Uppsala
fields.description: Uppsala is the county seat of Uppsala County and the fourth-largest city in Sweden, after Stockholm, Gothenburg, and Malmö. It had 177,074 inhabitants in 2019.

fields.name: Upplands Väsby
fields.description: Upplands Väsby is a locality and the seat of Upplands Väsby Municipality, Stockholm County, Sweden with 48,907 inhabitants in 2020.

fields.name: Örebro
fields.description: Örebro is the sixth-largest city in Sweden, and capital of the Örebro County. It has a population of approximately 126,000 in the city proper.

fields.name: Linköping
fields.description: Linköping is a city in southern Sweden, with around 105,000 inhabitants as of 2021.

fields.name: Helsingborg
fields.description: Helsingborg is the second-largest city in Skåne (after Malmö) and ninth-largest in Sweden, with a population of 113,816 (2020). Helsingborg is Sweden's closest point to Denmark.

fields.name: Jönköping
fields.description: Jönköping is a city in southern Sweden with 112,766 inhabitants (2022).

fields.name: Norrköping
fields.description: Norrköping lies about 160 km southwest of the national capital Stockholm. The city has a population of 95,618 inhabitants in 2016.

fields.name: Lund
fields.description: Lund is a city in the southern Swedish province of Skåne, across the Öresund strait from Copenhagen. The town had 91,940 inhabitants in 2018.

fields.name: Umeå
fields.description: Umeå is a city in northeast Sweden.

fields.name: Gävle
fields.description: Gävle had 77,586 inhabitants in 2020, which makes it the 13th most populated city in Sweden. It is the oldest city in the historical Norrland.

fields.name: Södertälje
fields.description: As of 2017, Södertälje has 72,704 inhabitants. Södertälje is located at Mälarens confluence in to the Baltic Sea through the lock in the Södertälje Canal.

fields.name: Borås
fields.description: Borås had 66,273 inhabitants in 2010. It is located at the point of two crossing railways, among them the railway between Gothenburg and Kalmar.
